==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Karyostenosis
<hw>Kar`y*o*ste*no"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>ka`ryon</grk> a nut, kernel + <?/ a being
straitened.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Direct cell division (in
which there is first a simple division of the nucleus, without any
changes in its structure, followed by division of the protoplasm of the
cell); -- in opposition to <contr>karyokinesis</contr>.</def> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Karyostenotic</ent>⟦br⟧
